HEADWORD: Estramacon
<hw>Es`tra`ma`con"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A straight, heavy sword with two edges, used in the
16th and 17th centuries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A blow with edge of a sword.</def>
<rj><au>Farrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Estrange</ent>⟦br⟧
